OL,3,CThousands of rail fare prosecutions
OL,4,Cset to be declared void
OL,6,FAt a hearing in June, Chief Magistrate
OL,7,FPaul Goldspring told Westminster
OL,8,FMagistrates' Court he believed the
OL,9,Fprosecutions were "void" and "probably
OL,10,Funlawful".
OL,12,FLawyers for rail companies told a
OL,13,Ffurther hearing last month they were
OL,14,F"in agreement" the cases should be
OL,15,Fquashed.
OL,17,FIn a ruling at the same court on
OL,18,FThursday, Judge Goldspring said six
OL,19,F"test cases" should be declared a
OL,20,F"nullity", so it was "as if as though
OL,21,Fthe proceedings never existed".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/18
