OL,6,FThe SJP was designed to deal with
OL,7,Fminor road traffic offences such as
OL,8,Fspeeding and driving without
OL,9,Finsurance, TV licence evasion and
OL,10,Fsimilar matters.
OL,12,FDefendants receive notice of the
OL,13,Fcharge by post. They have the option
OL,14,Fto plead guilty by post or online or
OL,15,Fto ask for a court hearing in person.
OL,17,FIf a defendant pleads "not guilty"
OL,18,Ftheir case will be transferred out of
OL,19,Fthe single justice procedure process,
OL,20,Fand listed for a in-person court
OL,21,Fhearing in the usual manner.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/18
