OL,6,FThe Magistrates' Association has
OL,7,Fpreviously expressed concerns that
OL,8,Fcases are being brought before
OL,9,Fmagistrates without prosecutors, such
OL,10,Fas the DVLA or TV Licensing, reading
OL,11,Fmitigations, and that many of its
OL,12,Fmembers are "uncomfortable" with the
OL,13,Fsystem.
OL,15,FThe exact number of those affected is
OL,16,Fcurrently unknown, with a previous
OL,17,Fhearing told around 75,000 people
OL,18,Fcould have been prosecuted for fare
OL,19,Fevasion offences under the SJP.
